With profound understanding of the importance of
								personal information to you, GLIZA will do its best to protect your personal information. We are
								committed to maintaining your trust in us and abiding by the following principles to protect your
								personal information: the principle of consistency of rights and responsibilities, the principle of
								explicit purpose, explicit consent principle, the principle of minimum sufficiency, the principle of
								security, the principle of subject participation and the principle of publicity and transparency, etc.
								Furthermore, GLIZA promises to take appropriate security measures to protect your personal information
								in accordance with the mature security standards in the industry. Please read and understand this
								Privacy Policy carefully before using our products (or services). We will prompt you to read this
								privacy policy when you first enter the product and ask you to choose whether to accept or not. If you
								choose to consent, GLIZA will collect and use your personal information strictly for the purposes
								described in this policy, as detailed in article 1 of this policy; If you choose not to, GLIZA will not
								automatically collect and report your personal information.
I. Our Collection and Use of Your Personal
								Information with your consent
Personal information refers to all kinds of
								information recorded electronically or otherwise that can identify the identity or reflect the activity
								of a specific natural person, either alone or in combination with other information. GLIZA will only
								collect and use your personal information out of the following purposes described in this
								Policy:
A. Business function two: Edit.
You may be required to
									grant the following permissions:(1) Album permissions: for reading and storing
									photos
If you refuse to grant any of the permissions above,
								the corresponding functions would not be realized. You can still use GLIZA for other
								functions.
When you edit a picture
									or video, the face information presented in this picture will be used. This face information is mainly
									used to identify the position of the face and facial features in the photo. Based on these positions,
									our application provides image editing functionalities. These face information data will only be used
									on your device, we will not collect and store it.
B. Business function three: In-app
								purchases
When you made in-app purchases in GLIZA, we will
								collect related order information , including IP address, unique device identification code, order
								number, transaction time, product category, product price and local language.
C. Business function four: Service optimization and
								in-time troubleshooting.
Your Device Id, IDFA,
									IP address, device model and operation log information may be collected to maintain the normal
									operation of service, troubleshoot products and improve and optimize services. The information
									necessary for service providing will be de-identified upon collection without being used to identify
									any specific user.
In the case of your
									feedback or consultancy to us, you are required to provide an Email address to contact you and help
									you to solve problems better
We will ask for your permission in advance of using
								your information for other purposes absent from the Policy.
II. Our Sharing, Transfer and Public Disclosure of
								Your Personal Information
A. Sharing
We will not share your personal information with any
								company, organization or individual other than Chengdu Painuo hudong Technology Co., Ltd., except as
								follows:
Sharing with explicit
									consent: we will share your personal information with other parties upon your explicit
									consent.
We may share your
									personal information externally in accordance with laws and regulations, need for litigation and
									dispute resolution, or compulsory requirements put forward by government authorities or judicial
									authorities.
We may provide your
									personal information for third parties when it is necessary for protecting Painuo and its users or the
									public interest, property or safety from damage to the extent required or permitted by
									law.
Sharing with authorized
									partners: some of our services will be provided by authorized partners. Currently, our authorized
									partners are only technical support partners, in order to complete the corresponding function, we will
									access to the third-party SDK for technical support. Such partners maybe asked to provide the
									following personal information, GLIZA may choose to use some of these partners in different periods or
									change partners, so the list of partners may be adjusted, see follow:
